nes">History of the separate disciplines</a><ul class="list-unstyled" data-level="h3"><li data-target="#ref38923"><a href="/web/20220202193947/https://www.britannica.com/topic/social-science/History-of-the-separate-disciplines#ref38923">Economics</a></li></ul><ul class="list-unstyled" data-level="h3"><li data-target="#ref38924"><a href="/web/20220202193947/https://www.britannica.com/topic/social-science/History-of-the-separate-disciplines#ref38924">Political science</a></li></ul><ul class="list-unstyled" data-level="h3"><li data-target="#ref38925"><a href="/web/20220202193947/https://www.britannica.com/topic/social-science/History-of-the-separate-disciplines#ref38925">Cultural anthropology</a></li></ul><ul class="list-unstyled" data-level="h3"><li data-target="#ref38926"><a href="/web/20220202193947/https://www.britannica.com/topic/social-science/Sociology">Sociology</a></li></ul><ul class="list-unstyled" data-level="h3"><li data-target="#ref38927"><a href="/web/20220202193947/https://www.britannica.com/topic/social-science/Sociology#ref38927">Social psychology</a></li></ul><ul class="list-unstyled" data-level="h3"><li data-target="#ref38928"><a href="/web/20220202193947/https://www.britannica.com/topic/social-science/Sociology#ref38928">Social statistics and social geography</a></li></ul></li></ul></li><li data-target="#ref345485"><a href="/web/20220202193947/https://www.britannica.com/topic/social-science/Sociology#ref345485">Social science from the turn of the 20th century</a><ul class="list-unstyled" data-level="h2"><li data-target="#ref345486"><a href="/web/20220202193947/https://www.britannica.com/topic/social-science/Sociology#ref345486">Science and social science</a></li></ul><ul class="list-unstyled" data-level="h2"><li data-target="#ref345487"><a href="/web/20220202193947/https://www.britannica.com/topic/social-science/Sociology#ref345487">Social science in the research universities</a></li></ul><ul class="list-unstyled" data-level="h2"><li data-target="#r